= About my OC "#ruby[らいは][礼羽]みや"

A carefree young lady from a magical world.

- Name: "礼羽みや" / "Miya Raiha"
- Birthday: December 24
- Age: 13
- Species: Human
- Occupation: A young lady does not need to work~

== Outfits

- Kimono outfit artist: akuma
- Spring outfit (Lolita) artist: 秋襟

== Appearance

- Height: 140 cm
- Hair color: Silver
- Eye color: Bright blue
- Hair clip: She usually wears a white hair clip, which is a very handy magical tool in this world.
- Hairstyle: Long hair with a single ponytail
- Bust size: B+ to C

== Personality

[
She likes silver and dislikes having her hair described as gray or white.

She likes meat buns and chocolate.
She likes coffee and afternoon tea.

She enjoys music, painting, literature, and all kinds of art centered on cuteness and beauty. She can easily lose herself in her own world.

She likes clean, simple surroundings.
Sometimes she spends the whole day in pajamas.
In everyday life, she is a bit of an airhead.

She loves staying at home. Other than attending family events, the number of times she chooses to go out in a year can be counted on one hand.

As a young lady who lives alone in a luxurious villa year-round, she has developed a quiet personality.
She does not like talking, does not like socializing, and never starts conversations with others on her own.

She is usually gentle and tolerant toward others, and almost always notices their strengths first.
She unconsciously shows a cute side of herself.
]

= Notes

In the first half of 2023, I started my illustration commission plan. Up to now, I have commissioned more than twenty illustrations, and along the way I was able to work with artists I had admired and receive pieces I really loved. Over the past year, because I commissioned several well-known artists, I went far over budget. On top of that, some artists I commissioned have been working rather slowly, so there have not been many new pieces for a while.

To keep up a steady update pace, at the start of 2026 I began this new small-treat plan: commissioning at least one small piece every month and posting it on the platforms.

